text:
If anyone&#x27;s interested in a super-easy way to embed an interactive chessboard on their own page, I very recently made a &lt;chess-board&gt; web component, forked from chessboard.js: <a href="https:&#x2F;&#x2F;justinfagnani.github.io&#x2F;chessboard-element&#x2F;" rel="nofollow">https:&#x2F;&#x2F;justinfagnani.github.io&#x2F;chessboard-element&#x2F;</a><p>You can put a board on a page with one tag:<p><pre><code>    &lt;chess-board&gt;&lt;&#x2F;chess-board&gt;
</code></pre>
And set it up via attributes:<p><pre><code>    &lt;chess-board
        draggable-pieces
        position=&quot;8&#x2F;R7&#x2F;8&#x2F;8&#x2F;k1K5&#x2F;8&#x2F;8&#x2F;8&quot;&gt;
    &lt;&#x2F;chess-board&gt;
</code></pre>
The element also has methods to make animated moves, set position, clear the board, etc.<p>I still have a few touch-interaction bugs to fix, so I haven&#x27;t submitted it to HN myself yet. I hope it&#x27;s useful to someone!
